        <h1>LeetCode 3512: Count Subarrays With Length Divisible by K (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums and an integer k. Return the total number of subarrays of nums where the length of the subarray is divisible by k. A subarray is a contiguous non-empty sequence of elements within an array.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3,4,5], k = 2<br/>
                Output: 6<br/>
                Explanation: The subarrays with length divisible by 2 are: [1,2], [2,3], [3,4], [4,5], [1,2,3,4], [2,3,4,5].<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [1,2], k = 1<br/>
                Output: 3<br/>
                Explanation: All subarrays have length divisible by 1: [1], [2], [1,2].<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [2,2,2,2,2], k = 3<br/>
                Output: 3<br/>
                Explanation: The subarrays with length divisible by 3 are: [2,2,2] (starting at index 0), [2,2,2] (starting at index 1), [2,2,2] (starting at index 2).
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    long long countSubarrays(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        long long count = 0;
        
        // Count subarrays of length divisible by k
        for (int length = k; length &lt;= n; length += k) {
            // Number of subarrays of this length
            count += n - length + 1;
        }
        
        return count;
    }
};</code></pre>
